---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ChapterNav from "../components/ChapterNav.astro";
---

<Layout title="Structured Logging with Log4j2 - SYP">
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-12 md:py-20">
        <a
            href="/syp-overview"
            class="mb-8 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300"
        >
            <span class="mr-2">&larr;</span>
            Back to SYP Overview
        </a>

        <article>
            <header class="mb-12">
                <h1
                    class="mb-4 text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl text-white"
                >
                    Structured Logging with Log4j2
                </h1>
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-400">
                    Implementing production-ready logging with file rotation,
                    levels, and structured output for observability
                </p>
            </header>

            <section class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8">
                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Overview</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                        Logging is how we understand what's happening in
                        production. I implemented Log4j2 with structured
                        logging, file rotation to prevent disk bloat, different
                        log levels for different purposes, and patterns that
                        make logs searchable and queryable. This is essential
                        for debugging issues and monitoring system health.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Learning Journey
                    </h2>
                    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300">
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                📝 Challenge: Choosing a Logging Framework
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Java has many logging frameworks (SLF4J,
                                java.util.logging, Logback). Chose Log4j2 for
                                better performance, async logging, and
                                fine-grained configuration control.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                💾 Challenge: Disk Space Management
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Applications log continuously. Log files grow
                                indefinitely without rotation. Configured
                                monthly rotation so old logs are archived and
                                new files start fresh each month.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                🔍 Challenge: Findable Logs
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Random log entries are useless. Implemented
                                structured logging with patterns including
                                timestamps, thread names, class names, and log
                                levels. Makes grep-ing through logs productive.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                ⚡ Challenge: Performance
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Disk I/O is slow. Configured async logging (via
                                queue) so logging doesn't block application
                                threads. Logs are buffered and written in
                                batches.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                ✅ Key Learning
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Structured logging with proper configuration is
                                foundational for operating systems in
                                production. It's often the only clue we have
                                when things go wrong.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Key Implementation
                    </h2>

                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">
                            Log4j2 Configuration (log4j2.xml)
                        </h3>
                        <div
                            class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden"
                        >
                            <pre
                                class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Configuration>
    <Properties>
        <!-- Log Pattern: Date | Thread | Class | Level | Message -->
        <Property name="LOG_PATTERN">%d{yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss} [%t] %-5p %c{1} - %m%n</Property>
    </Properties>

    <Appenders>
        <!-- Console Output (Development) -->
        <Console name="Console" target="SYSTEM_OUT">
            <PatternLayout pattern="%d{yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss} %highlight{%-5p}{FATAL=red, ERROR=red, WARN=yellow, INFO=green, DEBUG=blue, TRACE=blue} %c{1} - %m%n" />
        </Console>

        <!-- Rolling File Appender - Monthly Rotation -->
        <RollingFile name="RollingFile" fileName="logs/syp.log" filePattern="logs/%d{yyyy-MM}.log">
            <PatternLayout pattern="\${LOG_PATTERN}" />
            
            <!-- Trigger rotation at the beginning of each month -->
            <Policies>
                <TimeBasedTriggeringPolicy interval="1" modulate="true" />
            </Policies>
            
            <!-- Keep last 12 months of logs -->
            <DefaultRolloverStrategy max="12" />
        </RollingFile>

        <!-- Async Appender - Wraps RollingFile for non-blocking I/O -->
        <Async name="AsyncRollingFile" blockingQueue="RingBuffer" includeLocation="false">
            <AppenderRef ref="RollingFile" />
        </Async>
    </Appenders>

    <Loggers>
        <!-- Application Loggers -->
        <Logger name="com.example.syp" level="info" />
        
        <!-- Spring Framework (less verbose) -->
        <Logger name="org.springframework" level="warn" />
        
        <!-- Hibernate (SQL query logging - useful for debugging) -->
        <Logger name="org.hibernate.SQL" level="debug" />
        <Logger name="org.hibernate.type.descriptor.sql" level="trace" />
        
        <!-- Root Logger - All logs that don't match above -->
        <Root level="info">
            <AppenderRef ref="Console" />
            <AppenderRef ref="AsyncRollingFile" />
        </Root>
    </Loggers>
</Configuration>`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            Monthly rotation with timezone-aware triggers. Async
                            appender prevents logging from blocking application
                            threads. Keeps 12 months of history.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">
                            Using Log4j2 in Services
                        </h3>
                        <div
                            class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden"
                        >
                            <pre
                                class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`// UserService.java - Example Logging Usage
@Service
public class UserServiceImpl implements UserService {
    private static final Logger logger = LogManager.getLogger(UserServiceImpl.class);

    @Override
    public UserDto register(UserRegistrationRequest request) {
        logger.info("User registration request for: {}", request.getEmail());
        
        // Validate input
        if (request.getEmail() == null || request.getEmail().isEmpty()) {
            logger.warn("Invalid registration attempt: email is empty");
            throw new ValidationException("Email is required");
        }
        
        // Check for duplicate
        Optional<User> existing = userDao.findByEmail(request.getEmail());
        if (existing.isPresent()) {
            logger.warn("Registration attempt for existing email: {}", request.getEmail());
            throw new UserAlreadyExistsException("User already registered");
        }
        
        try {
            User user = new User();
            user.setEmail(request.getEmail());
            user.setPasswordHash(passwordEncoder.encode(request.getPassword()));
            
            User saved = userDao.save(user);
            logger.info("User registered successfully with ID: {}", saved.getId());
            
            return mapToDto(saved);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            logger.error("Error registering user: {}", request.getEmail(), e);
            throw new RuntimeException("Registration failed", e);
        }
    }

    @Override
    public Page<UserDto> getAllUsers(int page, int size) {
        logger.debug("Fetching users page {} with size {}", page, size);
        
        Pageable pageable = PageRequest.of(page, size, Sort.by("createdAt").descending());
        Page<User> users = userDao.findAll(pageable);
        
        logger.debug("Found {} users on page {}", users.getNumberOfElements(), page);
        return users.map(this::mapToDto);
    }
}`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            Different log levels: INFO for important business
                            events, WARN for potential issues, DEBUG for
                            debugging, ERROR for failures.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">
                            Log Files in Production
                        </h3>
                        <div
                            class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden"
                        >
                            <pre
                                class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`# Directory structure with monthly rotation
logs/
├── syp.log                 # Current month's logs (active file)
├── 2025-05.log             # May 2025 (archived)
├── 2025-06.log             # June 2025 (archived)
├── 2025-11.log             # November 2025 (archived)
└── ...

# Example log file content (syp.log)
2025-11-15 09:23:45 [main] INFO  UserServiceImpl - User registration request for: john@example.com
2025-11-15 09:23:46 [http-nio-8080-exec-1] INFO  UserServiceImpl - User registered successfully with ID: 42
2025-11-15 09:24:12 [http-nio-8080-exec-2] INFO  ItemServiceImpl - Fetching items page 0 with size 20
2025-11-15 09:24:13 [http-nio-8080-exec-2] DEBUG ItemServiceImpl - Found 20 items on page 0
2025-11-15 09:25:01 [http-nio-8080-exec-3] WARN  BidServiceImpl - Bid amount too low for item 5: current=€100, attempted=€95
2025-11-15 09:26:44 [async-exec-pool-1] ERROR EmailServiceImpl - Failed to send verification email to jane@example.com, cause: SMTP timeout

# Query logs with grep
$ grep ERROR logs/*.log                    # All errors
$ grep "item ID: 42" logs/*.log            # Find logs for specific item
$ grep -E "WARN|ERROR" logs/2025-11.log   # Warnings and errors this month`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            Structured format makes logs searchable with grep.
                            Monthly files prevent any single file from getting
                            too large.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Technology Stack
                    </h2>
                    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
                        {
                            [
                                "Log4j2",
                                "RollingFile Appender",
                                "Async Appender",
                                "PatternLayout",
                                "TimeBasedTriggeringPolicy",
                                "Structured Logging",
                            ].map((tech) => (
                                <span class="rounded-full border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/10 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-300">
                                    {tech}
                                </span>
                            ))
                        }
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Results & Impact
                    </h2>
                    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Searchable History:</strong> Months of logs
                                with clear structure, easy to grep/filter</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>No Disk Bloat:</strong> Monthly rotation
                                keeps disk usage predictable</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Non-blocking I/O:</strong> Async appender
                                prevents logging from slowing down requests</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Production-Ready:</strong> Works across environments
                                with same configuration</span
                            >
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </section>
            <ChapterNav
                prevLink="/syp-email-integration"
                prevText="Email Integration"
                nextLink="/syp-integration-testing"
                nextText="Integration Testing"
            />
        </article>
    </main>
</Layout>
